news.title: Residents of dilapidated building in Mumbai to be forcibly evicted, says BMC
news.para: Recently 19 people lost their lives after a dilapidated structure crashed in Kurla. The BMC willl issue a fresh notice to all residents living in these structures.

news.title: MHADA to undertake digital mapping, survey of its land parcels across Maharashtra
news.para: The housing board has already started the work and is currently in advanced stages of developing the Geographical Information System (GIS) driven mapping and Robotic Process Automation (RAP) systems for the same.

news.title: MahaRERA directs realtors to update projects progress in time bound manner
news.para: The move is aimed at bringing in more transparency and providing maximum information on public platforms. The regulator has issued a notification with regards to the standard operating procedure (SOP) that developers are expected to follow to maintain transparency.

news.title: Gurugram: Guesthouses flouting new rules under DTCP lens, to face action
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia said the government has already framed the new policy for operating guesthouses and those who are not following the norms will face action as per law.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Citizens raise a red flag as slum colonies mushroom on Parsik Hill
news.para: The residential part of the Parsik Hill faces fresh dangers of landslides and building collapses due to mushrooming of slum colonies, allege locals and environmentalists. They have also pointed out that retention wall around the hill is being usurped gradually for the purpose.

news.title: Bengaluru: Denied e-khata, many plot owners in limbo
news.para: Over 370 properties which were not approved for sale by BMRDA in Nelamangala and Bidadi were sold by the promoters, allegedly in connivance with officials from local town planning authorities.

news.title: Ranchi civic body to allot homes under PMAY via lottery on July 19
news.para: According to RMC officials, 1,521 applications were received by the civic body, of which 1,302 were shortlisted for lottery process which will be held on July 19 after thorough scrutiny.

news.title: About 400 housing societies granted deemed conveyance in Maharashtra
news.para: Of the 767 applications, 400 have been given deemed conveyance while 367 applications are pending, the officials said.

news.title: Indian Overseas Bank raises MCLR by 10 basis points
news.para: The one-year MCLR, the benchmark for most of consumer loans such as auto, personal and home, will be raised to 7.55 per cent from the existing 7.45 per cent.

news.title: CBI seizes Rs 34 crore worth of artwork during DHFL fraud searches
news.para: The agency conducted searches at the premises of Rebecca Dewan and Ajay Ramesh Nawandar in Mumbai and Dewan Villa in Mahabaleshwar, officials said.

news.title: Delhi court reserves order on Ansal brothers' appeal against seven-year-jail term
news.para: The case is related to tampering with the evidence in the main fire tragedy case in which the Ansals were convicted and sentenced to a 2-year jail term by the Supreme Court.

news.title: Panjab University property tax can't be waived: Chandigarh civic body
news.para: Sources said if the civic body gave any kind of relaxation to PU, then there were many educational and other institutions that would ask for it, leading to a major financial loss to the MC.

news.title: Over 375 houses, buildings in Delhi identified as dangerous or under structural stress
news.para: Saxena on June 27 instructed the MCD and New Delhi Municipal Corporation (NDMC) to identify dangerous buildings prone to collapsing during the rainy season and ensure their demolition or repair.

news.title: Unified Delhi civic body to come up with uniform property tax slab soon
news.para: The erstwhile MCD had come into being on April 7, 1958, evolving out of the municipal administration system that began around 1860s. It was trifurcated into North, South and East Delhi Municipal Corporations in 2012.

news.title: Pay property tax at centres, online in Coimbatore
news.para: ​​Corporation commissioner M Prathap urged residents to pay the revised property tax either at tax collection centres or online.
